=== STEP 2: Add the fetch ===
In the Promise.all([...]) block, add a third fetch AFTER the existing two:

EXISTING:
    Promise.all([
      fetch('/api/projects/'+encodedId).then(r=>r.json()),
      fetch('/api/queue').then(r=>r.json()),
    ]).then(([p, qdata])=>{

REPLACE WITH:
    Promise.all([
      fetch('/api/projects/'+encodedId).then(r=>r.json()),
      fetch('/api/queue').then(r=>r.json()),
      fetch('/api/projects/'+encodedId+'/github').then(r=>r.json()).catch(()=>null),
    ]).then(([p, qdata, ghData])=>{


=== STEP 3: Add helper functions ===
After the existing `const renderItem=(i)=>...` block, add:

      const timeAgo=(ds)=>{if(!ds)return'';const s=Math.floor((Date.now()-new Date(ds))/1000);if(s<60)return s+'s ago';if(s<3600)return Math.floor(s/60)+'m ago';if(s<86400)return Math.floor(s/3600)+'h ago';return Math.floor(s/86400)+'d ago';};
      const labelChip=(l)=>{const bg='#'+((l.color&&l.color!=='000000')?l.color:'333');const fg=labelFg(l.color);return`<span class="label-chip" style="background:${bg}33;border-color:${bg}88;color:${fg}">${escHtml(l.name||'')}</span>`;};
      const labelFg=(hex)=>{if(!hex||hex==='000000')return'#8b949e';const r=parseInt(hex.slice(0,2),16),g=parseInt(hex.slice(2,4),16),b=parseInt(hex.slice(4,6),16);return(r*299+g*587+b*114)/1000>128?'#0d1117':'#f0f6fc';};
      const escHtml=(s)=>s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;').replace(/"/g,'&quot;');

NOTE: If `esc()` is already defined in scope, use that instead of `escHtml`. The escaping function just needs to HTML-escape strings.


=== STEP 4: Build the issues+PRs panel HTML ===
After the line that renders the queue sections (after the `${!active.length&&!done.length?...}` ternary), add the GitHub panel. Insert this before the closing backtick of the template literal:

        ${ghData&&!ghData.error?`
        <div class="gh-panel card">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;margin-bottom:.85rem">
            <h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:600">🐙 GitHub</h2>
            <span>
              <span class="gh-fetched">fetched ${timeAgo(ghData.fetchedAt)}</span>
              <button class="gh-refresh-btn" onclick="refreshGitHub()">↻ Refresh</button>
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="gh-columns">
            <div>
              <div class="gh-col-header">
                <span>🔴 Issues <span style="color:#8b949e;font-weight:400;font-size:.85rem">(${(ghData.issues||[]).length} open)</span></span>
              </div>
              ${(ghData.issues||[]).length===0
                ?'<p class="gh-empty">No open issues ✓</p>'
                :(ghData.issues||[]).map(i=>`
                <div class="gh-item">
                  <div class="gh-item-title">
                    <span class="gh-num">#${i.number}</span>
                    <a href="${i.url}" target="_blank">${escHtml(i.title||'')}</a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="gh-meta">
                    ${(i.labels||[]).map(labelChip).join('')}
                    <span>${escHtml(i.author||'')}</span>
                    <span title="${i.createdAt}">${timeAgo(i.createdAt)}</span>
                    ${i.commentCount?'<span>💬 '+i.commentCount+'</span>':''}
                  </div>
                </div>`).join('')
              }
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="gh-col-header">
                <span>🟣 Pull Requests <span style="color:#8b949e;font-weight:400;font-size:.85rem">(${(ghData.prs||[]).length} open)</span></span>
              </div>
              ${(ghData.prs||[]).length===0
                ?'<p class="gh-empty">No open PRs ✓</p>'
                :(ghData.prs||[]).map(pr=>{
                  const reviewClass=pr.reviewDecision==='APPROVED'?'review-approved':pr.reviewDecision==='CHANGES_REQUESTED'?'review-changes':'review-pending';
                  const reviewLabel=pr.reviewDecision==='APPROVED'?'✓ approved':pr.reviewDecision==='CHANGES_REQUESTED'?'✗ changes req':'⏳ review pending';
                  const mergeClass=pr.mergeable==='MERGEABLE'?'merge-ok':pr.mergeable==='CONFLICTING'?'merge-conflict':'';
                  const mergeLabel=pr.mergeable==='MERGEABLE'?'mergeable':pr.mergeable==='CONFLICTING'?'⚠ conflicts':'';
                  return`<div class="gh-item">
                  <div class="gh-item-title">
                    <span class="gh-num">#${pr.number}</span>
                    ${pr.isDraft?'<span class="draft-badge">draft</span> ':''}
                    <a href="${pr.url}" target="_blank">${escHtml(pr.title||'')}</a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="gh-meta">
                    ${(pr.labels||[]).map(labelChip).join('')}
                    <span>${escHtml(pr.author||'')}</span>
                    <span class="${reviewClass}">${reviewLabel}</span>
                    ${mergeLabel?`<span class="${mergeClass}">${mergeLabel}</span>`:''}
                    <span title="${pr.createdAt}">${timeAgo(pr.createdAt)}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>`;}).join('')
              }
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>`
        :ghData&&ghData.error?`<div class="card gh-panel"><p class="gh-error">GitHub data unavailable: ${escHtml(ghData.error)}</p></div>`
        :'<div class="card gh-panel"><p class="gh-loading">GitHub data not available</p></div>'}


=== STEP 5: Add the refreshGitHub() function ===
In the <script> block, after the Promise.all block closes, add:

    function refreshGitHub() {
      const panel = document.querySelector('.gh-panel');
      if (panel) panel.style.opacity = '0.5';
      fetch('/api/projects/' + encodedId + '/github?refresh=1')
        .then(r => r.json())
        .then(() => location.reload())
        .catch(() => { if (panel) panel.style.opacity = '1'; });
    }


=== SUMMARY ===
The patch adds:
- CSS for the two-column GitHub panel, label chips, review/merge status indicators
- A third fetch in Promise.all for /api/projects/:id/github
- timeAgo(), labelChip(), labelFg(), escHtml() helpers
- Issues column: number, title (linked), label chips, author, age, comment count
- PRs column: number, draft badge, title (linked), label chips, author, review decision chip, merge status, age
- Refresh button that busts cache and reloads
- Graceful empty/error states
